{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"ad9aced9-02c4-4627-827a-1dfe05b22f05","content":"With xUnit v3 + MTP, the VSTest filter syntax (`--filter`) is replaced by **tree-node filters** (`--treenode-filter`).\n\nYour old filter:\n```\ndotnet test --filter \"FullyQualifiedName~IntegrationTests&Category=Smoke\"\n```\n\nTranslates to:\n```\ndotnet test --treenode-filter \"/**/IntegrationTests/**[Category=Smoke]\"\n```\n\n**Key differences:**\n\n| VSTest syntax | MTP tree-node syntax |\n|---|---|\n| `FullyQualifiedName~X` | `/**/X/**` (path glob) |\n| `Category=Smoke` | `[Category=Smoke]` (property filter in brackets) |\n| `&` (AND) | Combine path + property in one expression |\n\nThe tree-node filter treats tests as a tree: `/Assembly/Namespace/Class/Method`. Globs (`**`) match any segment. Properties (traits) go in `[]` appended to a node.\n\n**Also note:** In xUnit v3, `[Trait(\"Category\", \"Smoke\")]` still works, but you can also use the built-in `[Category(\"Smoke\")]` attribute if you prefer.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"f32ee5e7-0f33-4a8c-bae6-5dfc323a531a","outputTokens":290,"requestId":"9C42:1554C1:16238C1:18C11EC:69F861DA"},"id":"f054a7fa-7709-49d8-a587-28b6f8c938ce","timestamp":"2026-05-04T09:07:46.665Z","parentId":"52d315bb-c1f2-4c89-bd25-bfcf3df323f8"}
